OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1779714673
OL,3,CVillages lose water supply on hottest
OL,4,Cday of the year
OL,6,FSouth East Water has apologised to
OL,7,Fresidents of three Kent villages
OL,8,Fwho've had supply issues for more than
OL,9,F24 hours.
OL,11,FCharing, Challock and Molash first
OL,12,Fexperienced problems on at 8.30 on
OL,13,FSaturday morning, and were without
OL,14,Fwater for the hottest day of the year
OL,15,Fso far.
OL,17,FSouth East Water (SEW) said the issue
OL,18,Fwas resolved overnight on Saturday,
OL,19,Fbut that water supply problems resumed
OL,20,Fat about 9.30am on Sunday, citing
OL,21,F"issues with the pumping station".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/4
