OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,420,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1779714673
OL,3,CVillages lose water supply on hottest
OL,4,Cday of the year
OL,6,F"Residents feel abandoned, poorly
OL,7,Finformed, and unsupported throughout
OL,8,Fthis outage."
OL,10,FSEW said they were "sorry" to
OL,11,Fcustomers in the three villages who
OL,12,F"continue to experience water supply
OL,13,Fissues this morning".
OL,15,F"We know water supply issues during
OL,16,Fhot weather are deeply frustrating and
OL,17,Fincredibly disruptive," they said.
OL,19,FThey added their teams were "working
OL,20,Fhard" to restore tap water to
OL,21,Fcustomers as quickly as possible.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/4
